{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":973,"text":"2014 is a very special year for me:"},{"time":4107,"text":"20 years as a consultant,"},{"time":6034,"text":"20 years of marriage,"},{"time":7706,"text":"and I'm turning 50 in one month."},{"time":10887,"text":"That means I was born in 1964\nin a small town in Germany."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16437,"text":"It was a gray November day,"},{"time":18155,"text":"and I was overdue."},{"time":20035,"text":"The hospital's maternity ward\nwas really stressed out"},{"time":23518,"text":"because a lot of babies were born\non this gray November day."},{"time":28023,"text":"As a matter of fact,"},{"time":30145,"text":"1964 was the year with the highest\nbirth rate ever in Germany:"},{"time":34571,"text":"more than 1.3 million."},{"time":36591,"text":"Last year, we just hit over 600,000,"},{"time":39725,"text":"so half of my number."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41490,"text":"What you can see here\nis the German age pyramid,"},{"time":45321,"text":"and there, the small black point\nat the top, that's me."},{"time":48130,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":54307,"text":"In red, you can see the potential\nworking-age population,"},{"time":58440,"text":"so people over 15 and under 65,"},{"time":62689,"text":"and I'm actually only interested\nin this red area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66404,"text":"Now, let's do a simple simulation"},{"time":68447,"text":"of how this age structure will develop\nover the next couple of years."},{"time":72975,"text":"As you can see,"},{"time":74414,"text":"the peak is moving to the right,"},{"time":76713,"text":"and I, with many other baby boomers,\nwill retire in 2030."},{"time":83238,"text":"By the way, I don't need any forecasts"},{"time":85513,"text":"of birth rates for predicting\nthis red area."},{"time":88406,"text":"The red area,"},{"time":89678,"text":"so the potential\nworking-age population in 2030,"},{"time":93291,"text":"is already set in stone today,"},{"time":96589,"text":"except for much higher migration rates."},{"time":100141,"text":"And if you compare this red area in 2030\nwith the red area in 2014,"},{"time":106271,"text":"it is much, much smaller."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109382,"text":"So before I show you\nthe rest of the world,"},{"time":111820,"text":"what does this mean for Germany?"},{"time":115117,"text":"So what we know from\nthis picture is that the labor supply,"},{"time":119204,"text":"so people who provide labor,"},{"time":121131,"text":"will go down in Germany,\nand will go down significantly."},{"time":124800,"text":"Now, what about labor demand?"},{"time":127400,"text":"That's where it gets tricky."},{"time":130163,"text":"As you might know, the consultant's\nfavorite answer to any question is,"},{"time":134970,"text":"\"It depends.\""},{"time":136711,"text":"So I would say it depends."},{"time":139079,"text":"We didn't want to forecast the future."},{"time":141448,"text":"Highly speculative."},{"time":142957,"text":"We did something else."},{"time":144513,"text":"We looked at the GDP\nand productivity growth of Germany"},{"time":147903,"text":"over the last 20 years,"},{"time":149598,"text":"and calculated the following scenario:"},{"time":152082,"text":"if Germany wants to continue\nthis GDP and productivity growth,"},{"time":156563,"text":"we could directly calculate"},{"time":158676,"text":"how many people Germany would need\nto support this growth."},{"time":162647,"text":"And this is the green line: labor demand."},{"time":165619,"text":"So Germany will run into\na major talent shortage very quickly."},{"time":171331,"text":"Eight million people are missing,"},{"time":173165,"text":"which is more than 20 percent\nof our current workforce,"},{"time":175928,"text":"so big numbers, really big numbers."},{"time":178598,"text":"And we calculated several scenarios,"},{"time":180711,"text":"and the picture always looked like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184565,"text":"Now, to close the gap,"},{"time":186446,"text":"Germany has to significantly\nincrease migration,"},{"time":190509,"text":"get many more women in the workforce,"},{"time":192715,"text":"increase retirement age —"},{"time":194480,"text":"by the way, we just\nlowered it this year —"},{"time":196895,"text":"and all these measures at once."},{"time":199658,"text":"If Germany fails here,\nGermany will stagnate."},{"time":203721,"text":"We won't grow anymore. Why?"},{"time":206043,"text":"Because the workers are not there\nwho can generate this growth."},{"time":209456,"text":"And companies will look\nfor talents somewhere else."},{"time":213913,"text":"But where?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216730,"text":"Now, we simulated labor supply\nand labor demand"},{"time":220776,"text":"for the largest 15 economies in the world,"},{"time":223945,"text":"representing more than 70 percent\nof world GDP,"},{"time":227637,"text":"and the overall picture\nlooks like this by 2020."},{"time":231584,"text":"Blue indicates a labor surplus,"},{"time":234277,"text":"red indicates a labor shortfall,"},{"time":236762,"text":"and gray are those countries\nwhich are borderline."},{"time":240454,"text":"So by 2020, we still see a labor surplus\nin some countries,"},{"time":246560,"text":"like Italy, France, the U.S.,"},{"time":248743,"text":"but this picture will change\ndramatically by 2030."},{"time":253340,"text":"By 2030, we will face\na global workforce crisis"},{"time":257961,"text":"in most of our largest economies,"},{"time":260956,"text":"including three\nout of the four BRIC countries."},{"time":263371,"text":"China, with its former\none-child policy, will be hit,"},{"time":266529,"text":"as well as Brazil and Russia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270453,"text":"Now, to tell the truth,"},{"time":274168,"text":"in reality, the situation\nwill be even more challenging."},{"time":278974,"text":"What you can see here are average numbers."},{"time":282317,"text":"We de-averaged them"},{"time":284013,"text":"and broke them down\ninto different skill levels,"},{"time":286633,"text":"and what we found"},{"time":287950,"text":"were even higher shortfalls\nfor high-skilled people"},{"time":291884,"text":"and a partial surplus\nfor low-skilled workers."},{"time":296063,"text":"So on top of an overall labor shortage,"},{"time":299221,"text":"we will face a big\nskill mismatch in the future,"},{"time":303477,"text":"and this means huge challenges"},{"time":305200,"text":"in terms of education, qualification,"},{"time":307289,"text":"upskilling for governments and companies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312397,"text":"Now, the next thing we looked into\nwas robots, automation, technology."},{"time":318375,"text":"Will technology change this picture\nand boost productivity?"},{"time":323728,"text":"Now, the short answer would be"},{"time":325798,"text":"that our numbers already include\na significant growth in productivity"},{"time":330359,"text":"driven by technology."},{"time":333093,"text":"A long answer would go like this."},{"time":336628,"text":"Let's take Germany again."},{"time":339113,"text":"The Germans have\na certain reputation in the world"},{"time":341667,"text":"when it comes to productivity."},{"time":344244,"text":"In the '90s, I worked in our Boston office\nfor almost two years,"},{"time":348841,"text":"and when I left, an old senior partner\ntold me, literally,"},{"time":352998,"text":"\"Send me more of these Germans,\nthey work like machines.\""},{"time":356480,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":360967,"text":"That was 1998."},{"time":364259,"text":"Sixteen years later,\nyou'd probably say the opposite."},{"time":367742,"text":"\"Send me more of these machines.\nThey work like Germans.\""},{"time":371410,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378108,"text":"Technology will replace\na lot of jobs, regular jobs."},{"time":382811,"text":"Not only in the production industry,"},{"time":384808,"text":"but even office workers are in jeopardy"},{"time":386690,"text":"and might be replaced by robots,"},{"time":389521,"text":"artificial intelligence,\nbig data, or automation."},{"time":393120,"text":"So the key question is not\nif technology replaces some of these jobs,"},{"time":398042,"text":"but when, how fast, and to what extent?"},{"time":401688,"text":"Or in other words,"},{"time":403383,"text":"will technology help us\nto solve this global workforce crisis?"},{"time":409334,"text":"Yes and no."},{"time":411254,"text":"This is a more sophisticated\nversion of \"it depends.\""},{"time":414156,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":415227,"text":"Let's take the automotive industry\nas an example,"},{"time":420310,"text":"because there, more than 40 percent\nof industrial robots are already working"},{"time":424814,"text":"and automation has already taken place."},{"time":429332,"text":"In 1980, less than 10 percent\nof the production cost of a car"},{"time":434659,"text":"was caused by electronic parts."},{"time":437329,"text":"Today, this number is more than 30 percent"},{"time":440580,"text":"and it will grow\nto more than 50 percent by 2030."},{"time":445427,"text":"And these new electronic parts\nand applications"},{"time":449632,"text":"require new skills\nand have created a lot of new jobs,"},{"time":453652,"text":"like the cognitive systems engineer"},{"time":456223,"text":"who optimizes the interaction\nbetween driver and electronic system."},{"time":462081,"text":"In 1980, no one had the slightest clue\nthat such a job would ever exist."},{"time":469534,"text":"As a matter of fact,"},{"time":471051,"text":"the overall number of people\ninvolved in the production of a car"},{"time":475246,"text":"has only changed slightly\nin the last decades,"},{"time":478659,"text":"in spite of robots and automation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481677,"text":"So what does this mean?"},{"time":483443,"text":"Yes, technology\nwill replace a lot of jobs,"},{"time":485880,"text":"but we will also see a lot of new jobs\nand new skills on the horizon,"},{"time":491731,"text":"and that means technology will worsen\nour overall skill mismatch."},{"time":497768,"text":"And this kind of de-averaging"},{"time":499510,"text":"reveals the crucial challenge\nfor governments and businesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505175,"text":"So people, high-skilled people,"},{"time":509006,"text":"talents, will be the big thing\nin the next decade."},{"time":513046,"text":"If they are the scarce resource,\nwe have to understand them much better."},{"time":518688,"text":"Are they actually willing to work abroad?"},{"time":521637,"text":"What are their job preferences?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":524552,"text":"To find out, this year we conducted\na global survey"},{"time":529617,"text":"among more than 200,000 job seekers\nfrom 189 countries."},{"time":536021,"text":"Migration is certainly\none key measure to close a gap,"},{"time":541469,"text":"at least in the short term,"},{"time":543013,"text":"so we asked about mobility."},{"time":545613,"text":"More than 60 percent\nof these 200,000 job seekers"},{"time":550234,"text":"are willing to work abroad."},{"time":552834,"text":"For me, a surprisingly high number."},{"time":554994,"text":"If you look at the employees\naged 21 to 30,"},{"time":558407,"text":"this number is even higher."},{"time":560706,"text":"If you split this number up by country,"},{"time":564026,"text":"yes, the world is mobile, but only partly."},{"time":569227,"text":"The least mobile countries\nare Russia, Germany and the U.S."},{"time":574358,"text":"Now where would these people like to move?"},{"time":577632,"text":"Number seven is Australia,\nwhere 28 percent could imagine moving."},{"time":582462,"text":"Then France, Switzerland,\nGermany, Canada, U.K.,"},{"time":586804,"text":"and the top choice\nworldwide is the U.S."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590744,"text":"Now, what are the job preferences\nof these 200,000 people?"},{"time":594263,"text":"So, what are they looking for?"},{"time":597043,"text":"Out of a list of 26 topics,\nsalary is only number eight."},{"time":603475,"text":"The top four topics\nare all around culture."},{"time":608003,"text":"Number four,"},{"time":609558,"text":"having a great relationship with the boss;"},{"time":612554,"text":"three, enjoying a great work-life balance;"},{"time":616571,"text":"two, having a great relationship\nwith colleagues;"},{"time":620332,"text":"and the top priority worldwide"},{"time":623751,"text":"is being appreciated for your work."},{"time":628321,"text":"So, do I get a thank you?"},{"time":631152,"text":"Not only once a year\nwith the annual bonus payment,"},{"time":634496,"text":"but every day."},{"time":636701,"text":"And now, our global workforce crisis\nbecomes very personal."},{"time":641926,"text":"People are looking for recognition."},{"time":644967,"text":"Aren't we all looking\nfor recognition in our jobs?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":651302,"text":"Now, let me connect the dots."},{"time":654882,"text":"We will face a global workforce crisis"},{"time":657250,"text":"which consists\nof an overall labor shortage"},{"time":660222,"text":"plus a huge skill mismatch,"},{"time":662173,"text":"plus a big cultural challenge."},{"time":665307,"text":"And this global workforce crisis\nis approaching very fast."},{"time":669231,"text":"Right now, we are\njust at the turning point."},{"time":671971,"text":"So what can we, what can governments,\nwhat can companies do?"},{"time":676359,"text":"Every company,"},{"time":677962,"text":"but also every country,"},{"time":679749,"text":"needs a people strategy,"},{"time":681677,"text":"and to act on it immediately,"},{"time":684649,"text":"and such a people strategy\nconsists of four parts."},{"time":688596,"text":"Number one, a plan"},{"time":690407,"text":"for how to forecast supply and demand\nfor different jobs and different skills."},{"time":696537,"text":"Workforce planning will become \nmore important than financial planning."},{"time":702109,"text":"Two, a plan for\nhow to attract great people:"},{"time":705732,"text":"generation Y, women, but also retirees."},{"time":709865,"text":"Three, a plan for how to educate\nand upskill them."},{"time":713878,"text":"There's a huge\nupskilling challenge ahead of us."},{"time":717666,"text":"And four,"},{"time":719500,"text":"for how to retain the best people,"},{"time":722053,"text":"or in other words,"},{"time":723423,"text":"how to realize an appreciation\nand relationship culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731643,"text":"However, one crucial underlying factor\nis to change our attitudes."},{"time":738424,"text":"Employees are resources, are assets,"},{"time":742627,"text":"not costs, not head counts,"},{"time":745096,"text":"not machines,"},{"time":746505,"text":"not even the Germans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748176,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749302,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}